                    <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-gray-800">Community Health Outreach - Detailed Case Study</h4>
                    <img src="https://placehold.co/700x400/93c5fd/ffffff?text=Detailed+Project+1+Image" alt="Detailed Project 1" class="w-full h-auto object-cover rounded-lg mb-6 shadow-md">
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        This project involved planning, organizing, and leading health education and screening initiatives in various underserved communities. My role included assessing community needs, developing educational materials, and coordinating a team of volunteers to deliver services.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        **Challenges:** The primary challenge was reaching remote populations and overcoming logistical hurdles to provide accessible healthcare information and basic screenings. Ensuring cultural sensitivity in all educational materials was also crucial.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        **Solution:** We partnered with local community leaders and leveraged existing community centers to host events. I developed engaging, easy-to-understand health brochures and conducted interactive sessions on topics like disease prevention, hygiene, and maternal health.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        **Results:** The initiative successfully reached over 500 individuals, significantly increasing health awareness and facilitating early detection of common conditions. Post-event surveys indicated a 40% increase in participants' self-reported knowledge of preventative health measures.
